{
  "local_port": 43332,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you program a Dish network remote to a satellite receiver?",
  "response": "To program a Dish Network remote to a satellite receiver, follow these steps:\n\n### Method 1: Using the Remote's Setup Button\n\n1. **Turn on the Satellite Receiver:**\n   Ensure your satellite receiver is powered on.\n\n2. **Press the \"SAT\" Button:**\n   On your Dish Network remote, press the \"SAT\" button at the top of the remote. This will put the remote into satellite mode.\n\n3. **Press and Hold the Setup Button:**\n   Locate the \"Setup\" button (usually at the top of the remote, near the \"SAT\" button). Press and hold the \"Setup\" button until the \"SAT\" button blinks twice.\n\n4. **Enter the Satellite Code:**\n   Using the number keypad on the remote, enter the satellite receiver code. The most common code for Dish Network satellite receivers is `000`. If `000` does not work, you can try other codes such as `500`, `600`, or `810`. After entering the code, the \"SAT\" button should blink twice to indicate that the code was accepted.\n\n5. **Test the Remote:**\n   Try using the remote to control the satellite receiver. If it works, the programming is successful. If not, repeat the process with a different code.\n\n### Method 2: Using the Remote's Auto-Scan Feature\n\n1. **Turn on the Satellite Receiver:**\n   Make sure your satellite receiver is turned on.\n\n2. **Press the \"SAT\" Button:**\n   On your Dish Network remote, press the \"SAT\" button to put it into satellite mode.\n\n3. **Press and Hold the Setup Button:**\n   Press and hold the \"Setup\" button until the \"SAT\" button blinks twice.\n\n4. **Enter the Auto-Scan Code:**\n   Enter the auto-scan code `000` using the number keypad. The \"SAT\" button should blink twice.\n\n5. **Point the Remote at the Receiver:**\n   Point the remote at the satellite receiver and press the \"UP\" arrow on the remote. The remote will start scanning for the correct code.\n\n6. **Wait for Confirmation:**\n   When the remote finds the correct code, the satellite receiver will turn off. As soon as this happens, press the \"#\" (pound) button on the remote to lock in the code.\n\n7. **Test the Remote:**\n   Turn the satellite receiver back on and test the remote to ensure it is working correctly.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, ensure the batteries in the remote are fresh, and try the process again. If problems persist, you may need to contact Dish Network customer support for further assistance.",
